ZH: 我恰好在街上遇到了老朋友。
EN: I happened to run into an old friend on the street.

ZH: 这个机会恰好来得很合适。
EN: This opportunity came at just the right time.

ZH: 我今天恰好有空，可以陪你去买东西。
EN: I happen to be free today, so I can accompany you to go shopping.

ZH: 他在网上恰好看到了这篇文章。
EN: He happened to come across this article online.

ZH: 我恰好掌握了这个重要信息。
EN: I happen to possess this important information.

ZH: 她恰好和我有相同的兴趣爱好。
EN: She happens to share the same hobbies and interests as me.

ZH: 今天恰好是我们结婚纪念日。
EN: Today happens to be our wedding anniversary.

ZH: 他恰好是我正在寻找的人选。
EN: He happens to be the candidate I am looking for.

ZH: 这本书的内容恰好符合我的需求。
EN: The content of this book happens to meet my needs.

ZH: 我恰好来得早，所以没错过演出的开始。
EN: I happened to arrive early, so I didn't miss the beginning of the performance.

ZH: 他恰好在我最需要帮助的时候给了我支持。
EN: He happened to offer me support when I needed it the most.

ZH: 她恰好想起了这个重要的事情。
EN: She happened to remember this important matter.

ZH: 我来之前恰好下了场大雨。
EN: There happened to be a heavy rain before I arrived.

ZH: 我们恰好在同一个城市里度假。
EN: We happen to be vacationing in the same city.

ZH: 这件衣服的尺码恰好适合我。
EN: The size of this clothing happens to fit me perfectly.

ZH: 我恰好见过这位名人，他非常友善。
EN: I happened to meet this celebrity who was very friendly.

ZH: 这个问题的答案恰好在这本书里。
EN: The answer to this question happens to be in this book.

ZH: 那个餐厅恰好在我家附近。
EN: That restaurant happens to be near my home.

ZH: 他恰好是我最喜欢的歌手之一。
EN: He happens to be one of my favorite singers.

ZH: 这个地方恰好是我们要去的下一个目的地。
EN: This place happens to be our next destination.
